<abstract><t>This document describes an extension to IS-IS protocol [ISO10589], [RFC1195] to add an optional operational capability, that allows tagging and grouping ofthe nodes in an IS-IS domain.  This allows simple management and easy control over route and path selection, based on local configured policies.  This document describes the protocol extensions to disseminate per- node administrative tags in IS-IS protocols.</t></abstract>

